1. Create Table
Create a table named Employee with the following columns:
Column Name	Data Type	Description
employee_id	INT	Employee unique ID
employee_name	VARCHAR(50)	Name of the employee
employee_salary	DECIMAL(8,2)	Salary of the employee
department	VARCHAR(30)	Department of the employee
is_active	BOOLEAN	Status (TRUE = active, FALSE = inactive)

2. Alter Table – Add Column
Add a new column email of type VARCHAR(50) to the Employee table.

3. Alter Table – Modify Column Name
Rename the column employee_salary to salary.

4. Rename Table
Rename the table Employee to Employee_Details.

5. Insert Data (All Columns)
Insert the following employee records:
employee_id	employee_name	salary	department	is_active
201	Ravi	55000.50	IT	TRUE
202	Anitha	62000.75	HR	TRUE

6. Insert Limited Data
Insert a new employee with only employee_id and employee_name:
employee_id	employee_name
203	Kiran

7. Update Data
Update the salary of employee with employee_id = 203 to 48000.

8. Delete Data
Delete the employee record whose employee_id = 202.

9. Display All Data
Display all records from Employee_Details table.

10. Display Limited Columns
Display only employee_name and salary from Employee_Details.
